{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.10",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 10 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:1",
      "text": "A wise judge will instruct his people. The government of a man of understanding will be well ordered.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:2",
      "text": "As is the judge of his people, so are his officials. As the city’s ruler is, so are all those who dwell in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:3",
      "text": "An undisciplined king will destroy his people. A city will be established through the understanding of the powerful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:4",
      "text": "The government of the earth is in the Lord’s hand. In due time, he will raise up over it the right person at the right time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:5",
      "text": "A man’s prosperity is in the Lord’s hand. He will lay his honor upon the person of the scribe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:6",
      "text": "Don’t be angry with your neighbor for every wrong. Do nothing by works of violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:7",
      "text": "Pride is hateful before the Lord and men. Arrogance is abhorrent in the judgment of both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:8",
      "text": "Sovereignty is transferred from nation to nation because of injustice, violence, and greed for money.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:9",
      "text": "Why are dirt and ashes proud? Because in life, my body decays.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:10",
      "text": "A long disease mocks the physician. The king of today will die tomorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:11",
      "text": "For when a man is dead, he will inherit maggots, vermin, and worms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:12",
      "text": "It is the beginning of pride when a man departs from the Lord. His heart has departed from him who made him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:13",
      "text": "For the beginning of pride is sin. He who keeps it will pour out abomination. For this cause the Lord brought upon them strange calamities and utterly overthrew them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:14",
      "text": "The Lord cast down the thrones of rulers and set the lowly in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:15",
      "text": "The Lord plucked up the roots of nations and planted the lowly in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:16",
      "text": "The Lord overthrew the lands of nations and destroyed them to the foundations of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:17",
      "text": "He took some of them away and destroyed them, and made their memory to cease from the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:18",
      "text": "Pride has not been created for men, nor wrathful anger for the offspring of women.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:19",
      "text": "Whose offspring has honor? Human offspring who fear the Lord. Whose offspring has no honor? Human offspring who break the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:20",
      "text": "In the midst of kindred he who rules them has honor. Those who fear the Lord have honor in his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:22",
      "text": "The rich man, the honorable, and the poor all glory in the fear of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:23",
      "text": "It is not right to dishonor a poor man who has understanding. It is not fitting to glorify a man who is a sinner.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:24",
      "text": "The prince, the judge, and the mighty man will be honored. There is not one of them greater than he who fears the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:25",
      "text": "Free men will minister to a wise servant. A man who has knowledge will not complain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:26",
      "text": "Don’t flaunt your wisdom in doing your work. Don’t boast in the time of your distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:27",
      "text": "Better is he who labors and abounds in all things, than he who boasts and lacks bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:28",
      "text": "My son, glorify your soul in humility, and ascribe to yourself honor according to your worthiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:29",
      "text": "Who will justify him who sins against his own soul? Who will honor him who dishonors his own life?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:30",
      "text": "A poor man is honored for his knowledge. A rich man is honored for his riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.10.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 10:31",
      "text": "But he who is honored in poverty, how much more in riches? He who is dishonored in riches, how much more in poverty?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
